He was quick to note that they will be back next season which is scheduled to start in October.Wahome also coaches the men's team that features in the league. Kenya Army women's team has withdrawn from the ongoing Kenya Volleyball Federation (KVF) National League that enters second leg this weekend across three venues. 

The soldiers, who made a debut in the league in 2019 and finished seventh in the eight- team standings, skipped the first leg that was held last month in Nairobi. 



