"We intend to recruit heavily going forward and hopefully we will be ready for next season. Our focus now switches to the men's team and although we begun the league poorly, we hope to regroup and do better as the league gathers momentum." 

Kenya Army was scheduled to play former champions Kenya Pipeline this Saturday before taking on Kenya Defence Forces (KDF) on Sunday at the indoor Nyayo National Stadium, Nairobi. 

With Army's withdrawal,  the women's league remains with seven teams that features champions Kenya Prisons,  KCB Women's Volleyball Team, Pipeline, Directorate of Criminal Investigation, KDF,  league returnees Nairobi Water and new comers Nairobi Prisons. 



